Flowers bloom where you walk
lilies, roses and sunflowers sprout
Blossom in brilliant hues
A mosaic of longing and love
Draped in unwanted solitude
A whisper of the breeze,
Floating and wanning through
A lush of crimson kisses
Swarming my mind
While I soak in my gloom.
A golden glare,
The embrace of a southern typhoon
Ocean dapping at my hems
All beat down on my callused blues.

A love so good
Yet, meeting a fate that is so cruel
So grim
A graceless foredoom
One that strips bare a soul,
Heavily cocooned
Heart wrapped behind the thickest of skin
Fear tugged at every seam
Yet, it pierces through the sews
And tears my heavy linens and flesh

Oh, what a fool I am
What ignorance do I possess
To believe the heavens would grant me rest
To rest in your delicate embrace
To love a delicate heart
And be smothered by your hot breath
To ascend in you passion
And succumb in your hearth.

BY: Saron A.


